Building new package:
=====================

0. run qmake (it will generate the makefile, which is required later)
1. go to 'debian' directory and update all text files there;
2. return to this directory and type:

  dpkg-buildpackage -b

3. if the build was succesful a .deb package will be created in the directory
   above this one

QCA dependency:
=====================
0. Install libqca-qt5-2 from your distro repository if available
1. You can build libqca-qt5-2 from sources. Easy way: download source from http://packages.ubuntu.com/vivid/libqca-qt5-2. After building and installlig core libqca-qt5, you have to build and install plugin qca-ossl from plugins directory.

